        },
        {
          "id": "4f15bf1a1108_1",
          "href": null,
          "name": "97bc",
          "text": "The tragic mass shooting in Orlando is the natural outcome of our exploitative global economic system.",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*DonHlRcjjPNVD3ogC6E9Pw.png",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "OUTSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "4f15bf1a1108_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c775",
          "text": "Our media fails to connect the dots between an exploitative global economic system and violence around the world. It is very early (the shooting only happened a few hours ago) and already the US media is exploring possible linkages between the shooter and the Islamic State — drawing connections between the mass shooting epidemic in America and global terrorism.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "4f15bf1a1108_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4cb0",
          "text": "What you will not find in their reporting is the natural logic of extractive capitalism that created the economic conditions for both of these phenomena.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 87,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 49,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "4f15bf1a1108_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "115f",
          "text": "Anthropologists who study radical extremism have known that widespread economic desperation is an ideal environment for recruiting people to violent causes. (See here and here and here) Public health researchers have long known about the harmful effects of extreme wealth inequality on all manner of social ills, including violent behavior and criminal activities. Economic historians have closely scrutinized the breakdown of societies when a political elite controls too much wealth and power.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 166,
              "href": "http://www.nature.com/news/looking-for-the-roots-of-terrorism-1.16732",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 162,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 175,
              "href": "http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/nov/15/terrorists-isis",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 171,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 184,
